metadata.name: Burn Garden #26
metadata.description:
Burn Garden is a generative art work representing plants that grow as if they were fire. The plants burn different kinds of fruits that are a metaphor for NTF tokens that are created. The tokens become lighter, evolve, transfer and start floating in the sky as if they were pushed up by the hot air of the combustion
-	Hit ‘s’ to save a hi res (3072x3072) png file

metadata.name: Cubick (Neon Red) #44
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender Renders.

The variations are best viewed in live mode.

In each output, the four "cubes" are arranged in the same calming, 'zen-like' formation.

In each output, the orientation of the "cubes", and the number and positions of the colored regions varies.

All outputs in this collection will have the same color palette (called Neon Red).

In live mode:
Click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1375x1500px PNG.

Several "Cubick" collections will be released, each with a different color palette.

metadata.name: Provence #447
metadata.description:
The south of France namely the Provence has a cultural history of being an inspiration for impressionists and post-impressionists in the past.
For me personally the Provence is the place i was spending long, peaceful holidays as a child within beautiful nature.
This work does not so much aim for being realistic, rather than give an impression or feeling for this wonderful landscape. 
There are just a few different elements and concepts and yet there is variety of fascinating results.
I really hope you will enjoy your minting.

Notes:
STARTUP AND RENDERING MAY TAKE SOME TIME. (Up to 1min)
Code was written in typescript.
The only used libraries were chroma.js and simplex-noise

metadata.name: Sashiko #37
metadata.description:
This artwork is inspired by Sashiko - meaning 'little stabs' - which is the traditional Japanese method of repairing fabric with elaborate embroidery designs. This method makes the original fabric thicker, more durable and more beautiful. 
Here the plain coloured textiles take a back seat to the stitching, with simple palettes and layouts.
Keys 2, 3 and 4 will render the artwork at increasing resolutions.
